Count Down:
27 Days to My 19th birthday
i hate people and i hate life... this sounds so emo but i wish i could find someone who needs me as much as i need them
im depressed and i dont want to be here
someone shoot me...... im already tired of school.

my western civ prof got on his knees in the front of the class and begged people to read treasure island. it was really funny. he always goes off talking about what a nice day it is or what he did that morning, etc. its great.
I'm now on a low sodium diet. I can't eat anything!!!! I don't know what to do! Try looking at everything you have in your kitchen. then you'll see how hard this is for me.

I went to the doctor today to find out whats causing my kidney stones and they gave me a huge list of things i cant eat. 

Chocolate is on that list...

i am finally done with shopping...thank god. i am so ready to get this holiday over with...ugh. dont get me wrong, i love christmas, but i am so tired of all the political correctness. all the "happy holidays" and telling little kids that they can't perform at their school pageant because they chose songs about Christ. im tired of it. this is a RELIGIOUS HOLIDAY. everyone knows it so stop trying to secularize everything. its bullcrap. a school in LA banned an elemetary school choir because they wanted to sing "Joy to the World" and "Silent Night" but they allowed anything that was from hanukkah or kwanza (a made up holiday). so basically anything christian is banned. and do you know what that is?? it is called RELIGIOUS PERSECUTION. did you know that it takes courage for someone just to say "Merry Christmas"? yeah, christians are beaten down because they don't include everyone in their greetings. if you want to tell me "happy holidays" fine, do so, but dont expect me to give you the same greeting. This is Christmas, in celebration of the birth of My Savior. I dont care about the secular end of the holy-day. Would youi like to know what i do with my christmas morning? I dont wake up and run for all the gifts, I have been given. My family and I get up at 4 in the morning and drive to cincinnati where we prepare and serve breakfast to the homeless in a church downtown. I stand there and watch these men, women and children who have no where else to go, the shelters close during christmas, and i see the joy on their faces. i see, behind troubled eyes, a will to survive. and i count my blessings. with tears in my eyes, i pray to God and thank Him for everything I have. I watch the children, who won't get anything for christmas, come in with their parents and sit in hopes of a future. My heart aches for the families. 



A few years ago, when we first began making christmas breakfast for the homeless of cincinnati, we met a man who could not have been more joyful and thankful for all that God had given him. He had no material possessions, however, this man had in his keeping that which few others in his position can boast. He was so grateful of God's mercy and he had a heart to serve anyone and everyone as Christ commands. He accepted our service but he also wanted to give something back in appreciation for our kindness. We had given out hats, gloves, scarves and socks to all who came. This man, who had formed sort of an attachment to my younger sister, approached her and gave her the socks he had previously recieved, even though he was in desperate need of them. Not knowing what else to do my sister pushed them back towards him and said "They're too big for me, you keep them." He handed them to her again and replied "But I want you to have them. You'll grow into them someday." I watched all of this and cried because I saw a man in desperate need yet, he was willing to give away all he had to bring happiness to someone else. How selfish we are on this most holy day! to care about no one and nothing but what is waiting for us under the tree.

I hate emergency rooms, especially when they are overcrowded. I went again on monday and they put me in a room and left me in pain for an hour before anyone could see me. I didnt care how long they left me as long as they gave me drugs. thats all i really wanted.... but no, i could have done the IV myself if they just gave me the stuff. i just wanted the drugs, cant they understand that?? something to put me out of my misery......

by the way...

Its a boy...still don't have a name but it's 2mm long. ugh........ i don't want to ever go through that again. Well, umm, yeah. I'm proud of myself. I managed two kidney stones, (one during finals) and was still able to keep my grades up. ok...see ya bye.....

ok....this is my second kidney stone THIS WEEK!!!!! thats right two this week. one during finals on monday and one while i was christmas shopping last night. this is completly unfair. im only 18 and i've had three in one month. ugh......

well, this is fun. im taking my finals while on powerful pain meds. haha. i've gone through this whole day in a trance. i have two more finals to take today... ugh... but i have enough drugs to hold me over....hehehe.

finals start tomorrow and I HAVE ANOTHER KIDNEY STONE!!!!!!!!! yeah, not too happy. i really don't want to have to make up my finals. that would really suck. i jinxed myself last time by saying "well, atleast it isn't finals week."
NO MORE CLASSES!!! I have finals and thats it. Im done til next year. hehe

so yeah, i went to the Johnson Christmas party (guys dorm) with a friend to see her guy friend/love interest. she begged me to go and i did so reluctantly. put off my homework and finals studies. i will not do that again. once again i was the third wheel.
SNOW!!!!!!!!!!! IT'S SNOWING!!!!!!!! IM SO EXCITED!!!! ITS SNOWING, SNOWING, SNOWING!!!!!!!! well, actually it's ice BUT ITS STILL WHITE AND COVERING THE GROUND AND I WANNA GO OUTSIDE!!!

my parents bought a snack bag for me for finals. my heart was happy when I got it. you would not believe how much food is in this bag. it amazes me. and it was all organized through the school. parents send them money and the school gives us food. what fun.

Lauren's goodie bag includes:
chips 
cheezits 
pretzels 
animal crackers 
popcorn 
pringles 
cracker jacks 
ez mac 
chex mix 
crackers

OREOS 
candy (lots) 
hot chocolate mix

apple juice 
etc.
HAHA!!!!!   171/180!!!! second highest grade in the class on my bio lab exam. it was easy, but i can still gloat cant i??

Dear Santa...

Dear Santa,

This year I've been busy!

Last Wednesday I gave a kidney (1000 points). Last Friday I set 's puppy on fire (-66 points). In February I helped see the light (8 points). In May I got in line at the supermarket at the same time as someone else and I didn't yield (-8 points). In January I helped hide a body (-173 points).

Overall, I've been nice (761 points). For Christmas I deserve a toy train!

Sincerely,
needalifeudo

done with the first of six finals. not as bad as i expected. 


now to study for the other five...geez

I want to curl up in a ball and DIE!!!!!!! I am soooooo tired. I have my lab practical tomorrow that is worth half my grade. Im going in a minute to study for it. AND to top it all off, I AM PMSing. Im craving chinese food but im not about to buy $10 worth of food just so they deliver. Life sucks at the moment. I can't wait to go home for christmas. Next week is exams and they are all in the morning. Im gonna kill myself.

~*~ WoMeNs WoRdS ~*~ 


WORDS WOMEN USE ... 

FINE 
This is the word women use to end an argument when they are right and you need to shut up. 

FIVE MINUTES 
If she is getting dressed, this is half an hour. Five minutes is only five minutes if you have just been given 5 more minutes to watch the game before helping around the house. 

NOTHING 
This is the calm before the storm. This means "something," and you should be on your toes. Arguments that begin with 'Nothing' usually end in "Fine". 

GO AHEAD 
This is a dare, not permission. Don't do it! 

LOUD SIGH 
This is not actually a word, but is a non-verbal statement often misunderstood by men. A "Loud Sigh" means she thinks you are an idiot and wonders why she is wasting her time standing here and arguing with you over "Nothing". 

THAT'S OKAY 
This is one of the most dangerous statements that a woman can make to a man. "That's Okay" means that she wants to think long and hard before deciding how and when you will pay for your mistake. 

THANKS 
A woman is thanking you. Do not question it or faint. Just say you're welcome. 

WHATEVER 
It's a woman's way of saying F*** YOU!
i still feel like burning something.... or someone.... that would be fun too.

AHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHH!!!!!!!!!!!!!! left again!!!!!! Im beginning to think they dont like me. I really pissed off now and having fantasies about torching the place. I am so freakin tired of these people "wanting to include everyone" and then leaving them. They invited me. I said I would go downtown with them and to come and get me when they decided to leave. My roommate went with them and didnt even bother to tell me they were going. what is wrong with these people?? christian my ass. what a bunch of stuck up preachers kids. never think of anyone but themselves and the guys they plan to marry (who don't even know they exist). I am so freakin pissed off right now. 



i feel better now. not really...i think i'll go burn something.......

it's friday and i am alone...again...


i hate being invisible... i feel like doing something drastic, that would probably also get me kicked out of school. jeez...
My roommate might have to leave me next semester... ::cries::

hooray for fridays!!! 




however, i have a lot of work to do... i hate finals.

i can't help but think of my dad today. i don't know why, i just can't get him out of my head. i really miss him and i want to talk to him. i just...i don't know what to say. i don't know who he is anymore. thinking of him makes me want to cry. i have so many regrets, so many things i want to say to him but i can't find the words. he wouldn't understand half of it anyway. he doesn't like responsibility and none of what i want to say would mean much to him. i just miss him so much. i miss him being there, even though it was a long time ago, and i miss what could have been. sometimes i watch other people and their dads and think to myself "this is the way it should have been. this is what im missing." partly it's my fault. doug is more than willing to be there but im still waiting for my dad to step in. to ask forgiveness for the mistakes and to restart our relationship. im tired of waiting for him though. im tired of people telling me the phone line goes both ways. im just tired.





i have a paper to write for tomorrow. im not going to do it. im too tired and im pissed off. i just turned in a research paper on wednesday. give me a break. thank god i won't have to put up with her for much longer. i hate her class.

<lj-cut text="i am so bored">

 THINGS YOU CAN DO WITH ABSOLUTELY NOTHING

Push your eyes for interesting light show
(Amusement Potential: 1-5 minutes)
See a variety of blobs, stars and flashes. Try to make out things your subconscious is trying to send you a message? Can you control what you see by pressing different areas with different forces? Would it be possible to somehow see the same effects on TV?

See how long you can hold your breath
(Amusement Potential: 4-20 minutes)
Not that much fun, but it sure passes the time. Play with a friend, or try to beat your own personal best. Some tips: hyperventilate before hand, and stay as still as possible. My personal best is 2:00 (exactly).

Try to not think about penguins
(Amusement Potential: 1-5 minutes)
This is especially hard, because by trying too much, you remember what you were trying to avoid thinking of. If you try too little, you end up thinking about penguins anyway.

Use your secret mind power
(Amusement Potential: 5-10 minutes)
Pick a passing by and try to use your mind power to command them do something, like drop their bag or knock into someone. The law of averages dictates that sooner or later one of your mind commands will come true, so you can convince yourself that you really have super human powers and waste even more time trying them out.

Scratch yourself
(Amusement Potential: 1-3 minutes)
Go ahead, scratch yourself now. Even if nothing itches, go ahead. Doesn't that feel pretty good?

Repeat the same word over and over until it loses its meaning
(Amusement Potential: 1-3 minutes)
Pick a random word out of a magazine and say it aloud to yourself until it becomes a meaningless set of noises.

Hurt yourself
(Amusement Potential: 1-3 minutes)
What is pain? Why is it unpleasant? There's nothing physical about it - it's all in your mind. Plus, after pinching yourself for awhile, boredom will seem nice next to being in pain.

Try to swallow your tongue
(Amusement Potential: 1-3 minutes)
There's not much to say about this one. It is possible.

Pretend to be a car
(Amusement Potential: 1-3 minutes)
Make appropriate revving noises in your head as you walk along and add a racing commentary as you pass strangers in the street. Use blinking eyes as indicators for extra authenticity. 

Look at something for awhile, shut eyes, study after image
(Amusement Potential: 2-5 minutes)
Another great time waster. It takes about 30 seconds of staring to create an after image, and the image is then viewable for about the same length of time. Fun to combine this one with pushing on your eyes.

Get yourself as nauseated as possible
(Amusement Potential: 5-10 minutes)
Best achieved by looking straight up and spinning around. Try to be so dizzy you can't even stand up. This is also entertaining due to the "makes boredom seem a lot better" effect (see "Hurt Yourself"). 

 

 THINGS YOU CAN DO WITH VERY LITTLE

See what's in your neighbour's rubbish/trash
(Amusement Potential: 20-30 minutes)
You can learn a lot about people by what they throw out. You might uncover some dark secret about them. Plus, they might be throwing out something with value that still works, like a VCR or some porn mags.

Watch TV, repeat everything said in Italian accent
(Amusement Potential: 5-10 minutes)
Sort of entertaining. Include flamboyant shoulder shrugs for added impact, or go for a Marlon Brando set of grunts. 

Send spooky emails
(Amusement Potential: 15-60 minutes)
Look up someone's CV on the web, do some research on them via Google and then send them an email full of personal references claiming to be an ex-work colleague who fell in love with their shoes. Or something.

Play our useless games
(Amusement Potential: how long have you got?)
Waste away the hours with our collection of useless games

Make prank phone calls
(Amusement Potential: 20-60 minutes)
Very entertaining, but requires discipline. Remember - vulgarities don't make a call funny, but getting the other person to believe a ridiculous story will. Try seeing if you can get them to make noises to 'test' the line. One to get you started off: Call McDonalds with weird complaints about their food.

Pretend all humans will die except for people in room with you
Amusement Potential: 10-20 minutes)
What would you do if this really happened? Would the group stay together, or would there be factions? Who would join what group? Remember, there would only be power for a few days before the plants ran out of fuel or broke. To travel, you would always have to be near cars to siphon gas out of. Best to do with people you know.

Step off a curb with eyes shut, imagine it's a cliff
(Amusement Potential: 2-5 minutes)
To get any benefit out of this one, you have to have a good imagination. Don't step off immediately, build up to the jump. Study the ravine below. Feel the winds at that altitude. Step off and...AHHHHHH!!!!!

Try and sound Welsh
(Amusement Potential: 1-3 minutes)
The key to sounding Welsh is to make sure that your voice goes up at the end of the sentence, so that everything sounds like a question. Throw in a superfluous 'isn't it?' at the end of everything you say and you're halfway there. Isn't it? 

Burn things with a magnifying glass
(Amusement Potential: 5-30 minutes)
Ants are always fun to use for this, but burning the face of someone you don't like, under some circumstances, can be just as entertaining. 

 

 THINGS YOU CAN DO WITH ANOTHER PERSON

Have a water drinking contest
(Amusement Potential: 5-10 minutes)
While the competition is fun, you probably won't feel too good afterward. To give your event an old western theme, slam the cups upside down on the tables after you have emptied them.

Stare at the back of someone's head until they turn around
(Amusement Potential: 2-5 minutes)
This works on the "I have the feeling I'm being watched" principle. Conduct an experiment-does this really work?

Have a "Who is less competitive" competition
wonder (Amusement Potential: 1-3 minutes)
Trying to win at this will make you lose. Trying to lose makes you win which makes you lose. Not trying at all makes you lose which makes you win which makes you lose.

Pick up a dog so it can see things from your point of view
(Amusement Potential: 3-5 minutes)
Think about it: your dog has only seen the house from a viewpoint from 6" to 2' high (15 to 60 cm for all you metric fans). It's never seen the tops of counters, what you keep on your desk, the tops of shelves, etc. Try looking at things from its point of view, too.

Pull out a hair, stick in someone's ear
(Amusement Potential: 1-5 minutes)
Best done to sleeping people. Added challenge in having no one else around, because then you can't blame it on anyone else. Try to beat your record number of times before the person catches on.

Pour water in hand, make sneeze noise, throw water on back of person's neck
(Amusement Potential: 5-15 minutes)
Always a good gag. For an even bigger reaction out of the person, act like you're not sorry at all for what they think you did. Comment instead on how big that sneeze was or about how there was a lot of mucus in that one.

</lj-cut>
